        <p id="Par34">To test and validate this capability, we simulated outbreaks with time-varying delay distributions, as described in “<xref rid="Sec36" ref-type="sec">Appendix C</xref>” section. The delay from infection to observation gradually changed from a short to a long delay (or vice versa) over the course of the simulated outbreak. Auto-correlated observation noise was added to the simulated observations. We then estimated <inline-formula id="IEq52"><alternatives><tex-math id="M115">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
