        <p id="Par44">On this simulated data, all three methods yield comparable results, with estimateR performing most accurately. It achieves a consistently high coverage and low error, and more accurately follows abrupt <inline-formula id="IEq69"><alternatives><tex-math id="M183">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
