        <p id="Par45">We note that a certain degree of model misspecification could explain the comparatively worse performance of epidemia and, to a lesser extent, of EpiNow2. For both packages, we specified negative binomial observational models, whereas noise in the simulated data results from Poisson noise when generating infections combined with log-normal noise when generating observations. epidemia offers the option to specify a log-normal observation model, but we did not manage to set up an analysis with this option (the inference either failed or returned diverging <inline-formula id="IEq72"><alternatives><tex-math id="M189">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
