          </sec>
          <sec id="Sec34">
            <title>Uncertainty estimation</title>
            <p id="Par76">To account for the uncertainty in the raw case observations, a 95% bootstrap confidence intervals is constructed for <inline-formula id="IEq182"><alternatives><tex-math id="M359">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$R_{e}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M360"><mml:msub><mml:mi>R</mml:mi><mml:mi>e</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5428_Article_IEq182.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. First, the case observations are re-sampled as follows: given the original case observations <inline-formula id="IEq183"><alternatives><tex-math id="M361">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
