            <p id="Par78">Finally, the bootstrap case observations are obtained by<disp-formula id="Equ10"><label>10</label><alternatives><tex-math id="M401">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned} D_t^* = \max (\exp ({\hat{h}}_t + e^*_t) -1, 0). \end{aligned}$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M402" display="block"><mml:mrow><mml:mtable><mml:mtr><mml:mtd columnalign="right"><mml:mrow><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>D</mml:mi><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mo>∗</mml:mo></mml:msubsup><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mo movablelimits="true">max</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mo>exp</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>h</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover><mml:mi>t</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mo>+</mml:mo><mml:msubsup><mml:mi>e</mml:mi><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mo>∗</mml:mo></mml:msubsup><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>-</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn><mml:mo>,</mml:mo><mml:mn>0</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow><mml:mo>.</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mtd></mml:mtr></mml:mtable></mml:mrow></mml:math><graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5428_Article_Equ10.gif" position="anchor"/></alternatives></disp-formula>The smoothing-deconvolution-estimation method is applied to the bootstrap case observation to obtain an estimate for <inline-formula id="IEq203"><alternatives><tex-math id="M403">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$R_{e}(t)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M404"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi>R</mml:mi><mml:mi>e</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5428_Article_IEq203.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>, denoted by <inline-formula id="IEq204"><alternatives><tex-math id="M405">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${{\hat{\theta }}}^*(t)$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M406"><mml:mrow><mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mover accent="true"><mml:mi>θ</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">^</mml:mo></mml:mover></mml:mrow><mml:mo>∗</mml:mo></mml:msup><mml:mrow><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mi>t</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:mrow></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5428_Article_IEq204.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula>. By repeating the above steps <italic>B</italic> times (<inline-formula id="IEq205"><alternatives><tex-math id="M407">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$B = 100$$\end{document}</tex-math><mml:math id="M408"><mml:mrow><mml:mi>B</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>100</mml:mn></mml:mrow></mml:math><inline-graphic xlink:href="12859_2023_5428_Article_IEq205.gif"/></alternatives></inline-formula> by default), we obtain <inline-formula id="IEq206"><alternatives><tex-math id="M409">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
